Step 1: Identify the key components for FCF calculation. In this context, the FCF is calculated as the net cash flow from operating activities minus the capital expenditure (i.e. purchase of fixed assets).

Step 2: Based on the provided data:
  • Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities = -650630.22
  • Purchase of Fixed Assets = 0.00

Step 3: Calculate FCF:
  FCF = Operating Cash Flow – Capital Expenditures
  FCF = -650630.22 - 0.00 = -650630.22

Thus, the Free Cash Flow (FCF) is -650630.22.
